column1: # Neanderthal Introgression — Adaptive Segments (Low / Medium / High)
# Segments the genome into contiguous regions of constant introgression class
# based on per-SNP frequencies, limited to pilot-mask intervals (≤1 kb gaps bridged).
# - Adjacent SNPs with the same class form one segment.
# - Segments are created only within bridged pilot-mask intervals.
# - START_POS = first SNP position in segment
# - END_POS   = last SNP position in segment
# Length              → Segment length in base pairs (bp)
# avg_freq            → Mean introgressed allele frequency across SNPs in segment
# SNP_total           → Total number of SNPs in segment
# SNP_0               → Count of SNPs with FREQ = 0 (no introgression)
# Adaptive segmentation per chromosome (1–22) using low/medium/high introgression states.
# Mask gaps ≤ 1 kb are bridged; segments do not cross unmasked regions.
# Output is tab-separated (.tsv) and includes comment header.
# avg_recomb_rate     → Mean recombination rate (cM/Mb) across the segment, from GLIMPSE recombination map.
# SNP_Neand_Specific  → Number of Neanderthal-specific mutation SNPs within the segment.
# - Adjacent segments are merged across mask gaps if compatible:
# - All counts are summed; avg_freq is SNP_total-weighted; avg_recomb_rate is segment-length-weighted.
# - introgression is reassigned from merged avg_freq.
# available_bp        → Fraction of merged span covered by actual segments (0–1).
# Additional columns added from 10 kb bin overlap:
# bin_low       → Number of overlapping 10 kb bins labeled 'low' (SNP_Neand_Specific == 0)
# bin_low_NSS   → Number of overlapping 10 kb bins labeled 'low' (SNP_Neand_Specific > 0)
